@baseUrl = http://localhost:5081

### Health check — IEndpoint<TResponse>, AllowAnonymous
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

### List users — [FromQuery] pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users?page=1&pageSize=2
Accept: application/json

###

### List users — filter by role
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users?role=Admin&page=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Find user by ID — [FromRoute], EndpointContext header
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Find user by ID — Accept-Language header demo
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Accept: application/json
Accept-Language: ja

###

### Find user — 404 (ID does not exist in dummy data)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/999
Accept: application/json

###

### Create user — POST body binding, DataAnnotations validation (valid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Eve",
  "email": "eve@example.com",
  "role": "User"
}

###

### Create user — 400 validation error: invalid email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Eve",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

###

### Create user — 400 validation error: name too long (>100 chars)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA",
  "email": "toolong@example.com"
}

###

### Update user — multipart/form-data, BindAsync
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Alice Updated
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

alice-updated@example.com
------Boundary--

###

### Delete user — EmptyResponse 204 No Content
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1

###

### Admin stats — [FromQuery] date range, group-level filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/stats?from=2025-01-01&to=2025-12-31
Accept: application/json

###

### Admin stats — defaults (last 30 days)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/stats
Accept: application/json
